    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n527" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀλέομαι, ἀλεύομαι</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀλέϝομαι</span>), aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἠλεύατο, ἀλεύατο, -ντο</span>, opt. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀλέαιτο</span>, imp. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄλευαι,
            ἀλέασθε</span>, inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀλέασθαι</span>,
          part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀλευάμενος</span> (subj. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀλέϝηται, ἀλεϝώμεθα</span>, aor. or pres.):
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">shun, avoid, flee from, flee;</span> abs., and freq.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τί</span>, rarely <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τινά</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">θεούς</span>, ‘shun their
          wrath,’ <i><span class="en">Od. 9.274</span></i>); also w.
          inf.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
